'''Gedolim pictures''' are photos or sketches of (or attributed to) famous [[rabbi]]s, known as [[Gadol|gedolim]] admired by Jews.
It is a cultural phenomenon found largely in the [[Orthodox Judaism|Orthodox]] and [[Haredi Judaism|Haredi]] Jewish communities. Gedolim pictures are pictures of famous rabbis and other prominent Jews which are circulated amongst the Jewish communities. Quite frequently, these pictures are posted on the walls of offices, businesses, houses, and schools where Jews are present.
Collecting Gedolim pictures has developed into a hobby for many Jewish children around the world; it is similar to collecting [[sports cards]]. {{multiple image | width = 79 | footer = | image1 = Vilna Gaon authentic portrait.JPG | alt1 = Vilna Gaon | caption1 = [[Vilna Gaon]] | image2 = Yitzchak Zev Soloveitchik.jpg | alt2 = Yitzchak Zev Soloveitchik | caption2 = [[Yitzchak Zev Soloveitchik|Brisker Rov ]] | image3 = Medini 1.jpg | alt3 = Chaim Hezekiah Medini | caption3 = [[Chaim Hezekiah Medini|Sede Chemed]] | image4 = Shlomo Ganzfried.jpg | alt4 = Shlomo Ganzfried | caption4 = [[Shlomo Ganzfried]] | image5 = Chaim Yosef David Azulai.jpg | alt5 = Chaim Yosef David Azulai | caption5 = [[Chaim Yosef David Azulai|Chida]] | image6 = Meir Shapiro.jpg | alt6 = Meir Shapiro | caption6 = [[Meir Shapiro]] | image7 = Schneur Zalman of Liadi.jpg | alt7 = Schneur Zalman of Liadi | caption7 = [[Schneur Zalman of Liadi|Baal ha-Tanya]] }} {| class="wikitable" |[[File:Steipler Gaon.jpg|center|95px]] |[[Image:Yitzchak Elchanan Spektor.jpg|center|100px|]] |[[Image:Shmuel Salant.jpg|center|100px|]] |[[Image:Avraham Mattisyahu of Shtefanesht.JPG|center|100px|]] |<!-- Deleted image removed: [[Image:Husiatyn Reb Yisroel.jpg|center|100px|]] --> |[[Image:Reb Chaim Ozer.jpg|center|100px|]] |[[Image:Yisrael Meir Kagan.jpg|center|110px]] |}
